+# `@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus`
+
+The Reckoner petition-scheduler. Provides the kit-static petitioner registry,
+`guild.json` configuration, priority types with default-filling, and the
+`reckoner.petition()` / `reckoner.withdraw()` helper APIs.
+
+A petition is a writ in `new` phase carrying `writ.ext['reckoner']`. The
+Reckoner is one authority among several that can transition writs out of `new`;
+the CDC handler that watches held writs and decides their fate is a separate
+downstream commission.
+
+See also: [`docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md`](../../../docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md).
+
+---
+
+## Installation
+
+```sh
+pnpm add @shardworks/reckoner-apparatus
+```
+
+Register the apparatus in `guild.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "plugins": [
+    "@shardworks/clerk-apparatus",
+    "@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus"
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## Configuration
+
+The Reckoner reads its config from `guild.json` under the `reckoner` key:
+
+```json
+{
+  "reckoner": {
+    "enforceRegistration": false,
+    "disabledSources": []
+  }
+}
+```
+
+| Key | Type | Default | Description |
+|-----|------|---------|-------------|
+| `enforceRegistration` | `boolean` | `false` | When `true`, petitions from unregistered sources are declined (writ cancelled). When `false` (default), a warning is logged and the writ proceeds. |
+| `disabledSources` | `string[]` | `[]` | Per-source disable list. Petitions from any source in this array are skipped by the Reckoner — left in `new` phase indefinitely. Used by the CDC-handler commission. |
+
+---
+
+## API
+
+```typescript
+interface ReckonerApi {
+  /**
+   * Post a writ in `new` phase with Reckoner ext set correctly.
+   * Validates source, applies priority defaults, calls clerk.post() then
+   * clerk.setWritExt(). Returns the persisted WritDoc.
+   */
+  petition(request: PetitionRequest): Promise<WritDoc>;
+
+  /**
+   * Withdraw a held writ by transitioning it to cancelled.
+   * Thin wrapper around clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', {resolution}).
+   */
+  withdraw(writId: string, reason?: string): Promise<WritDoc>;
+}
+```
+
+Retrieve via `guild().apparatus<ReckonerApi>('reckoner')`.
+
+---
+
+## Petitioner registration
+
+Petitioners declare themselves via a `petitioners` kit contribution:
+
+```typescript
+// in your kit or apparatus supportKit
+export default {
+  kit: {
+    requires: ['reckoner'],
+    petitioners: [
+      {
+        source:      'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+        description: 'Vision-vs-reality snapshots emitted when drift is observed.',
+      },
+    ],
+  },
+};
+```
+
+**Source id grammar:** `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}` — the contributing plugin's
+derived id, a literal `.`, then a kebab-case suffix (lowercase letters, digits,
+single-hyphen separators). Malformed ids hard-fail at startup.
+
+The registry is **kit-static**: contributions are consumed at boot and sealed at
+`phase:started`. Duplicate source ids are a hard startup error naming both
+contributing plugin ids.
+
+---
+
+## Posting a petition (Workflow 2 — canonical)
+
+```typescript
+const reckoner = guild().apparatus<ReckonerApi>('reckoner');
+
+const writ = await reckoner.petition({
+  type:     'mandate',
+  title:    'Address vision drift detected at 04:00 UTC',
+  body:     'Drift score exceeded threshold …',
+  codex:    'nexus',
+  source:   'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: {
+    visionRelation: 'vision-violator',
+    severity:       'serious',
+    scope:          'major-area',
+    time:           { decay: true, deadline: null },
+    domain:         ['quality'],
+  },
+  complexity: 'bounded',
+  payload:    { driftScore: 0.87 },
+  labels:     { 'vision-keeper.io/vision-id': 'nexus' },
+});
+// writ.phase === 'new'
+// writ.ext['reckoner'] === { source, priority, complexity, payload, labels }
+```
+
+**Priority defaults.** Any omitted dimension falls back to:
+
+```
+visionRelation: 'vision-neutral'
+severity:       'minor'
+scope:          'minor-area'
+time:           { decay: false, deadline: null }
+domain:         []
+```
+
+---
+
+## Direct posting (Workflow 1 — always available)
+
+Any apparatus can post a Reckoner-gated writ without calling `reckoner.petition()`:
+
+```typescript
+const writ = await clerk.post({ type, title, body, codex });
+await clerk.setWritExt(writ.id, 'reckoner', {
+  source:   'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: { visionRelation: 'vision-violator', /* ... */ },
+});
+```
+
+The CDC handler inspects `writ.ext['reckoner']` regardless of which workflow
+created the writ; both paths produce identical Reckoner behavior.
+
+---
+
+## Withdrawing a petition
+
+```typescript
+await reckoner.withdraw(writId, 'Snapshot superseded — newer drift detected.');
+// or via Clerk directly:
+await clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', { resolution: '…' });
+```
+
+---
+
+## Priority types
+
+```typescript
+type Priority = {
+  visionRelation: 'vision-blocker' | 'vision-violator' | 'vision-advancer' | 'vision-neutral';
+  severity:       'critical' | 'serious' | 'moderate' | 'minor';
+  scope:          'whole-product' | 'major-area' | 'minor-area';
+  time:           { decay: boolean; deadline: string | null };
+  domain:         Array<DomainTag>;
+};
+
+type DomainTag =
+  | 'security' | 'compliance' | 'cost' | 'feature' | 'quality'
+  | 'infrastructure' | 'documentation' | 'research' | 'ergonomics';
+
+type ComplexityTier = 'mechanical' | 'bounded' | 'exploratory' | 'open-ended';
+```
+
+Use `defaultPriority(partial?)` to fill defaults programmatically:
+
+```typescript
+import { defaultPriority } from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+
+const p = defaultPriority({ visionRelation: 'vision-violator' });
+// { visionRelation: 'vision-violator', severity: 'minor', scope: 'minor-area', … }
+```
+
+---
+
+## Dependencies
+
+- **Required:** `@shardworks/clerk-apparatus` — `petition()` and `withdraw()` both
+  call into `ClerkApi`.
